25|$|After a gap of {{over ten}} months the Palmach resumed operations. <b>The</b> one weapon <b>of</b> {{which there was}} no {{shortage}} was locally produced explosives. On 20 May 1947 they blew up a coffee house in Fajja, specifically in retaliation for <b>the</b> murder <b>of</b> two Jews in nearby Petah Tikva. Following <b>the</b> <b>escalation</b> <b>of</b> violence after <b>the</b> UN Partition Resolution <b>the</b> scale <b>of</b> <b>the</b> retaliation operations increased.|$|R
